Muslims across the country have been admonished to eschew violence and embrace the virtue of the prophet Mohammed as they celebrate this year’s Eid-el Kabir. Lucy Izoduwa Omagbon who reflected on the need to live together as a country with diverse cultures and beliefs harped on the benefits of respecting one another’s religion as a people bonded with the constitutional sentiments. Lucy Omagbon who is seeking to represent the Ovia Federal Constituency on the platform of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP Edo State, gave the admonition while rejoicing with Muslim faithful in her constituents and by extension, the state. Hon. Omagbon believes that the hope of building a strong and veritable country is underpinned by trust, equity, and fairness, adding, ” it’s a time to correct our mistakes and ask God for total forgiveness” The grassroots political Omagbon urged religious leaders to continue to emphasize moral voluptuary to live the right legacy for the upcoming generations. She enjoined citizens to brace up, and not lose hope amidst the heightened security challenges currently bedevilling the country while urging a rededication towards the creator of mankind.